# Game Sandbox Rule

Every user-created game is a **self-contained static asset**, not a React component.

## File structure

```
frontend/public/games/{game-name}/
  index.html      # The entire game: HTML + CSS + JS in one file
  thumbnail.png   # Optional screenshot for the gallery
```

- The main site renders each game inside an `<iframe src="/games/{game-name}/index.html">`.
- Vite copies `public/` into `dist/` at build time, so games are served as-is with no bundling.

## Boundaries

- **NEVER** modify files under `frontend/src/` when building or editing a game.
- **NEVER** add game logic to `App.tsx` or any React component.
- **NEVER** install npm packages for game code. Games must have zero build-step dependencies.
- Game files go in `frontend/public/games/{game-name}/` and nowhere else.
- One game = one folder = one `index.html`.
